        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 30 at 11:37AM CDT until April 30 at 12:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
McCurtain County in southeastern Oklahoma...
Northern Red River County in northeastern Texas...

* Until 1230 PM CDT.

* At 1137 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
from 30 miles northwest of Manchester to 25 miles west of Bogata,
or along a line from 45 miles northwest of Clarksville to 28 miles
northwest of Hagansport, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Idabel, Broken Bow, Manchester, Bagwell, Wright City,
Valliant, Detroit, Millerton, Haworth, Garvin, Oak Hill, Golden,
Glover, Holly Creek, Farmers Hill, Hochatown, Slim, Albion and
Mount Herman.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT Wednesday for
portions of southeast Oklahoma and northeast Texas.</instruction>
